<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0001 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 20:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nyerere Praised For Efforts To Help Burundians Enter Into Dilogue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(By Pei Shanqin)
</P>
<P>
ARUSHA (TANZANIA), March 14 (Xinhua) -- Presidents of Kenya,
Uganda and Tanzania today commended former Tanzanian President
Julius Nyerere for his efforts to promote understanding among
various political forces in Burundi and help them enter into
dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan president Daniel Arap Moi, Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni and Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa today met in
Arusha, Northern Tanzania, to inaugurate the Secretariat of the
East African Co-operation (EAC).
</P>
<P>
A communique signed today by the three presidents said that
the three heads of state had held talks on bilateral, regional
and international issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
With regard to Burundi, the communique said, the three
presidents consulted with J.K. Nyerere, who was present at the
relaunching of the EAC, on the current political situation in
Burundi and his task of promoting a political solution to the
crisis in Burundi in order to realize an enduring peace and
stability in the country.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that the three leaders "expressed their
full support to the laudable efforts of Mwalim Nyerere and urged
him to persist in the search for durable peace and national
concord among the people of Burundi" whose lives have been torn
apart by conflicts. They called upon the international community
to render full support to Mwalimu Nyerere in his efforts to find
lasting peace and stability in Burundi.
</P>
<P>
The three leaders also called upon the people and particularly
"the leaders of Burundi to sieze this opportunity to find a
lasting solution to their national problems," said the
communique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
