<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 19:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC States Hold Joint Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and other Arab Gulf
states today started a joint exercise in the Acaira area, north of
Kuwait, on withdrawals and counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwait News Agency quoted a Defense Ministry statement as
saying that the war game was in line with the "Desert Shield 5"
exercises.
</P>
<P>
Desert Shield groups forces from the Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) states -- Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates,
Bahrain, Oman and Qatar.
</P>
<P>
The Commander of the Desert Shield Force, Major General
Abdullah Al-Shadoukhi, and Commander of the Kuwaiti Forces, Major
General Salem Masoud, supervised the exercise.
</P>
<P>
The final phase of this exercise, due to be held on Saturday,
will be attended by Kuwaiti Defense Minister Sheikh Ahmad Al-Hmoud
Al-Sabah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
