<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Killed In Traffic Accident In Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed and 14
injured in a serious traffic accident in Mozambique's southern
Gaza Province, the Mozambican Information Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy happened near the province's capital Xaixai
yesterday when a truck dashed against a minibus full of
passengers.
</P>
<P>
The traffic accidents have frequently taken place in
Mozambique in recent years, mainly caused by drink-driving and
driving over speed limit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
