<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 19:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 500,000 Demobilized Soldiers Resettled In Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's Commission for
the Rehabilitation of Former Soldiers and Disabled War Veterans
has terminated its mandate and begun transfering its offices,
projects and movable and immovable properties to regional states.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Deputy Commissioner of the oganization
Alemayehu Haile Mariam here today.
</P>
<P>
Haile Mariam said that since the establishment of the
commission in 1991, it has made commendable efforts in resettling
and integrating over 500,000 demobilized soldiers of the former
government into the society.
</P>
<P>
The commission has begun transfering its projects and
furniture at the headquarters here and its 19 branch offices to
regional governments, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the over 350 workers of the commission are going
to be transferred to other government offices in line with their
profession. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
