<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 18:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AL Chief Calls for Continuation of Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the
Cairo-based Arab League (AL) Esmat Abdul Meguid today made a fresh
call for boosting the sluggish Middle East peace process following
the conclusion of an international anti-terrorism summit held in
Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Meguid made the call while has addressing the the 105th session
of the Arab League Council, which opened at the AL premises here.
</P>
<P>
Meguid said that the AL's secretariat had sent letters on the
peace drive to the United States and Russia, co-sponsors of the
peace process, and to the Italian government that currently serves
as chairman of the European Union.
</P>
<P>
He said that the convening of the anti-terrorism summit, or
summit of peacemakers in the Egyptian Red Sea city of Sharm el
Sheikh Wednesday, has demonstrated international determination and
world support for a peaceful settlement to the Middle East
problems.
</P>
<P>
"The Middle East region does not stand alone in the face of
difficulties that obstruct the process of peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
In its letters, the AL secretariat also emphasized the
importance of maintaining and bolstering the peace process, saying
that the Arab nation calls for peace and is keen on the prevalence
of a just, comprehensive and lasting peace in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Meguid noted that the Arab world would never enjoy security and
stability until after a just and comprehensive settlement,
including the Palestinian people's right to establish its
independent state, is materialized in the region.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the summit of peacemakers, the AL chief said the
summit's closing statement clearly reflected the desire to salvage
peace at a time when all roads to peace seemed to have reached a
dead end.
</P>
<P>
In this context, Meguid stressed the necessity of a immediate
resumption of the peace process on all tracks without
delay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
