<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 19:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Businessmen Urged To Reduce Food Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Congress of Trade
Union (ZCTU) today appealed to businessmen to reduce prices of
mealie meal (maize flour), the staple food of Zambians.
</P>
<P>
ZCTU President Alec Chirwa told reporters in northern city of
Kitwe that traders who sell food must also have a moral
obligation of selling products at affordable prices to consumers.
</P>
<P>
Chirwa said it was inhuman for the traders to hike food prices
which would make customers fail to buy and this would result in many
children dying from malnutrition.
</P>
<P>
"The government must work hard to ensure that price of mealie
meal becomes affordable to every Zambian," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He urged the government to improve the food marketing
system and promote competition among traders, adding that this
was the only way of reducing prices of food.
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, the average price of mealie meal has
been hiked by some 40 percent due to shortage of maize in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
