<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Training For UNCDF Officers Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 14 (Xinhua) --United Nations Capital
Development Fund (UNCDF) field implementation officers drawn from
13 African and Asian countries opened a six-day training here
today.
</P>
<P>
The training, organized by UNCDF and opened by its Executive
Director Poul Crossen, aims at broadening the understanding of
the officers regarding the relationship between the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP) and its special fund, the
UNCDF and exposing them to the new goals and products of the
fund, a press release said.
</P>
<P>
The fund, which spends about 2 million Dollars annually in
Ethiopia, is currently financing low cost housing, electricity
supply, road construction and other development projects, the
release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
