<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 17:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Meets with Turkish President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
today met with visiting Turkish President Suleyman Demirel in
Gaza, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference following the meeting, Arafat, who
returned to Gaza today from Egypt's Red Sea resort of Sharm
El-Sheikh where he attended the peacemakers summit Wednesday,
termed the conference as "successful and positive."
</P>
<P>
He said the summit's final statement demonstrated this
success. World leaders, who attended the summit, expressed their
insistence on preserving peace and following up progress in
implementation of the summit resolution through a special committee
involving representatives from all the participating countries,
Arafat added.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Turkish President Demirel said that Turkey was
ready to contribute to the infrastructure and reconstruction
projects in the Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
Demirel hoped to further boost Turkish-Palestinian economic and
trade relations.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope that the closure of the West Bank and
Gaza Strip imposed by Israel would come to an end as soon as
possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
