<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe To Transform Social Security Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's National Social
Security Authority (NSSA) General Manager Rory O'Shea said today
the authority is undergoing a major transformation into an
efficient public service institution.
</P>
<P>
"Old NSSA was too bureaucratic and had staff with a siege
mentality who suspected every application," said O'Shea.
</P>
<P>
He assured Zimbabweans that within the next few months, NSSA
would be operational with re-trained staff to provide a fast,
efficient and satisfactory service to the public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
