<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 17:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> COMESA Ministers To Meet In April In Lusaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Council of Ministers of the
Common Market of Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) will meet
in Lusaka, Zambia, on April 18, Secretary-General Bingu Wa
Mutharika said here today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is to review COMESA programs and formulate new
strategies for this year, said Mutharika.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting would also review the progress made in the
implementation of the various COMESA programs during 1995 and
adopt the Program of Action for this year.
</P>
<P>
The secretary general added that the council would adopt the
annual budget of the COMESA secretariat, and discuss the summit
of the COMESA heads of state and government.
</P>
<P>
The date of the summit is yet to be announced.
</P>
<P>
The COMESA leaders will discuss the dual membership of the
Southern African Development Community (SADC) states.
</P>
<P>
Two SADC members, South Africa and Zimbabwe, have declined to
ratify the treaty establishing COMESA -- a regional grouping
formed in 1992 to create a common market in eastern and
southern Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
