<HEADLINE> Weightlifter Petrov Tests Positive For Steroids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 14 (Xinhua) -- World champion Russian
weightlifter Alexei Petrov tested positive for anabolic
steroids at the World Championships in China in November, the
International Weightlifting Federation (IWF) said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We have notified the Russian federation of the positive
result of the A sample and are awaiting a request from Moscow to
test sample B," IWF general secretary Tamas Ajan said.
</P>
<P>
According to the IWF rule, Petrov, gold medal winner in the
91-kg category, is facing a possible two year suspension from
competitions including the Atlanta Olympic Games this summer.
</P>
<P>
A total of 64 lifters were tested positive from 1301 samples
before the World Championships last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
