<HEADLINE> 5 Israelis Wounded by Hezbollah Guerrillas in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT March 14 (Xinhua) -- Five Israeli soldiers were wounded
by guerrillas of Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, this
afternoon in an attack at an Israeli military convoy in the
Israeli-occupied enclave in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas launched the bomb attack at the Israeli convoy on a
road between the towns of Aishiyeh and Rihan in Jezzine area in
northern sector of the Israeli self-proclaimed "security zone" in
south Lebanon, according to security sources in the south.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the guerrillas detonated an explosive devise
near the town of Aishiyeh at 3:20 p.m. (13:20 GMT) when the
Israeli convoy comprising several military vehicles was passing
by.
</P>
<P>
At least one vehicle was destroyed and five Israeli soldiers
were wounded, one of them is in dangerous condition, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Beirut, the Islamic Resistance, the
military wing of Hezbollah, claimed responsible for the attack.
</P>
<P>
Radio of the Israeli-backed South Lebanon Army militia
confirmed that the Israeli positions at Sejoud, Rihan and Khazlan
were attacked this afternoon by guerrillas, but denied any
casualties.
</P>
<P>
Israeli occupation forces, on the other hand, bombarded today
a number of suspected guerrilla bases in Iglim Al-Toffah in the
afternoon, causing no casualties, the security sources said.
</P>
</TEXT>
