<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 15:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Downs South Korea in Four-nation Women's Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, Zhenjiang Province, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Olympic and
world runners-up China held off a tenacious challenge from South
Korea to clinch their first victory at the third leg of the
four-nation women's basketball tournament here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese players, who lost to the Cubans at the opening game
on Wednesday, edged out the South Koreans 87-81 after leading
45-43 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese jumped to a 11-4 lead with an aggressive game, but
the South Koreans closed the gap soon with fast attack and
well-knit defense and surged ahead 12-11 on a three-pointer by
Kwun Eun-Jeong.
</P>
<P>
Then began a see-saw game. China had snatched lead twice
before South Korea made it 43-43 with only 30 seconds to go in the
first half.
</P>
<P>
Liang Xin converted a foul shot to put China 45-43 ahead at the
interval.
</P>
<P>
China led by 11 points five minutes into second half, but their
lead was soon eroding under South Korea's well-organized attacks.
</P>
<P>
South Korea levelled the score 72-72 with four minutes
remaining.
</P>
<P>
In the final minutes, the host team cashed in on some defensive
errors by the South Koreans to pull away.
</P>
<P>
"I'm not satisfied with my team's performance today," said
Chinese head coach Chen Daohong. "The South Koreans snatched lead
from our hands quite a few times while we were leading by about 10
points. That means my team is inexperienced and immature."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese coach didn't see a bright prospect for his team in
the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"I will be very happy with a third-place finish in Atlanta, "
Chen said. "If China falls to fifth or sixth place, I won't be
surprised."
</P>
<P>
"Unlike the world championship last year, we now only have
Zheng Haixia to count on," he added.
</P>
<P>
The 2.04-meter Zheng, the most valuable player in the world
championship, scored a game-high 37 points in Thursday's match and
pumped in 32 points, also a game-high, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other game, the United States beat Cuba 81-78
after leading the halftime 38-37.
</P>
<P>
The United States won the first two legs of the tournament in
Haikou and Zengcheng respectively a few days ago, twice beating
China into the second place.
</P>
<P>
Cuba placed third twice with South Korea last. 
</P>
</TEXT>
