<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 15:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Budgets for 1996 Are Feasible </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The draft budgets of the central
and local governments for 1996 conform with the state properly
tight fiscal policy and are expected to support economic and
social advancements.
</P>
<P>
This is the view of an examination report on the draft budgets
made by the Financial and Economic Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
The report was approved this afternoon at the second meeting of
the presidium of the Fourth Session of the Eighth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Li Hao, vice-chairman of the committee, made the report at the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
According to the draft budgets, budgeted revenues will see
certain increases, the increase rate of budgeted expenditures will
be lower than that of budgeted revenues, deficit will be cut, the
state will increase investment in agriculture, science and
education despite the properly right fiscal policy, Li Hao said in
his report.
</P>
<P>
This year begins the country's Ninth Five-year Plan, and it is
of great significance to arrange and implement budgets of central
and local governments well, so that China's reform, development
and stability can maintain a strong momentum, Li Hao said.
</P>
<P>
For years, wealth distribution has tilted markedly in favor of
individuals. State fiscal revenues now account for less than 11
percent of the gross domestic product (GDP). Under such
circumstances, the functions of the governments cannot be fully
carried out, Li said.
</P>
<P>
In order to fulfill the 1996 central and local budgets, the
committee proposed that relevant departments strive to increase
revenues by collecting taxes strictly according to law, control
financial expenditures by implementing the tight financial policy,
strengthen disciplines and supervision over financial operations
and further carry out taxation reform.
</P>
<P>
Li said that implementation of the 1995 central and local
budgets was generally good, with state revenues increasing
considerably, and expenditures basically meeting the needs of
major projects and development of various governmental
undertakings.
</P>
<P>
But the problems are that the proportion of financial revenues
in GDP keeps dropping, enforcement of the tax law is lax, and tax
evasions are rampant, according to him.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that to realize the goal of boosting the nation's
financial strength in the next five years, the financial and
taxation mechanism must be further improved, initiatives of
governments at all levels should be brought into full play to
collect more and spend less.
</P>
<P>
The central and local governments's responsibilities for
various revenues and expenditures must be clarified in accordance
with the budget law, and the financial transfer payment system
should be fully established and further improved, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
