<HEADLINE> Italian Soccer Players to Strike This Weekend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The strike of Italian soccer players
will go ahead as planned this weekend, announced Sergio, Campana,
head of the players union, in Milan on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The players are in dispute with the Italian Football Federation
over payments into a players' pension fund and the use of foreign
players.
</P>
<P>
The strike means there will be no matches either Saturday, when
the four clubs involved in next week's European cup ties -- AC
Milan, Juventus, Parma and AS Roma -- were all due to play, or on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Campana had announced the strike on Monday and immediately
concessions were made by Italian Football Federation chief Antonio
Matarrese and a plea to call off the action came from the
government.
</P>
<P>
But Campana was unimpressed. He also boycotted a meeting in
Rome with Matarrese on Thursday aimed at trying to finding a
solution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
