<HEADLINE> All-time Tennis Great Borg Comes Back to HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Five-time Wembledon tennis
singles champion Bjorn Borg of Sweden is going back to Hong Kong
later this year, the first time in 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Borg, who celebrates his 50th birthday in June this year, will
compete in the NatWest Markets Tennis Classic scheduled on November
20-23 this year.
</P>
<P>
Sanctioned by the Hong Kong Tennis Association (HKYA), this is
the first event on the burgeoning ATP Senior Tour slated this year
for Asia.
</P>
<P>
Romania's showman supreme Ilie Nastase, strong-willed Stan
Smith from the United States and Iranian-born Mansour Bahrami have
also confirmed their participation in the 84,000 U.S. dollars
tournament.
</P>
<P>
The ice-cool Borg won five consecutive Wimbledon titles from
1976 and 11 Grand Slam titles in all during his glittering career
while the charismatic Nastase lifted an amazing 57 singles titles
and 51 doubles titles in the Open series, five of them in Grand
Slam tournaments.
</P>
<P>
Smith defeated Nastase in an epic five-set final to win the
1972 Wimbledon singles title for his second Grand Slam singles
finals of fifteen tournaments winning five titles.
</P>
<P>
The tournament will be split into three sections - doubles,
shoot out and singles. The 12 players will be paired off into six
doubles teams and play in two groups with the winners of each group
contesting in the final.
</P>
<P>
In the shoot out, six players aged 45 and over will compete in
a knockout singles competition. The matches will be the best of
three tie-break encounters.
</P>
<P>
The over-35s will play two singles sets with a 12 point
tie-break deciding a tied match. All finals will be played on
November 23.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
