<HEADLINE> Philippines' Fiber Exports up in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' fiber export
earnings reached 100 million US dollars in 1995, up 13.5 percent
from 88 million US dollars in 1994, the country's Fiber Industry
Development Authority (FIDA) said today.
</P>
<P>
FIDA attributed the rise to a growing demand for Manila hemp in
the world markets.
</P>
<P>
The volume of fiber exports totaled 169,222 bales last year
compared with 157,616 bales in 1994, said FIDA.
</P>
<P>
Manila hemp made up the bulk of the Philippines' fiber exports,
accounting for about 91.3 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
