<HEADLINE> APEC to Remove Trade Barriers for Small Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum has agreed to remove tariff and
non-tariff barriers for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs)
of its member economies in export, reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached by 77 delegates at a three-day
organizational workshop that opened here Wednesday on the APEC
Center for Technology Exchange and Training for SMEs.
</P>
<P>
The delegates said the removal of these barriers would enhance
economic competitiveness and increase business opportunities in
the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
However, Brunei said it hopes the relaxation of trade barriers
should take into consideration the different levels of SME
development among various APEC economies.  
</P>
