<HEADLINE> India Unveils Plan to Boost Relations with ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- India has spelt out a
seven-point action plan for expanding its economic relations with
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), the Indian
Express reported today.
</P>
<P>
The plan was unveiled at a symposium here Wednesday by External
Affairs Minister Pranab Mukherjee as ASEAN has agreed to accept
India as a full dialogue partner of the grouping.
</P>
<P>
Mukherjee said the government and the business community of
India should make a joint massive effort for "India brand imaging"
in ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
This effort had to be preceded by expanding the information
base that India had on individual ASEAN countries and on the new
ASEAN matrix of trade and economic relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance to refurbish India's image in the
eyes of ASEAN's trade and industry sectors, which, he said, often
viewed India as an uncompetitive giant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
