<HEADLINE> Regional Development For North China Discussed (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They enumerated the region's major advantages.
</P>
<P>
-- With 1.2 million scientific and technological workers, the
region's comprehensive scientific and technological strength ranks
first in the country;
</P>
<P>
-- With Beijing as the country's railway and telecoms hub,
Tianjin and Qinhuangdao as two major seaports in northern China,
the region boasts a well-developed transport and telecoms network;
</P>
<P>
-- With Tianjin as a traditional industrial base and commercial
hub in northern China, and Hebei providing a variety of farm
produce and mineral resources, it is well-balanced in economic
structure.
</P>
<P>
-- With a population of 80 million, the region presents a vast
market whose present retail sales account for over ten percent of
the nation's total.
</P>
<P>
High-ranking local officials have paid frequent visits to one
another in recent years, discussing ways and fields of
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
To expand cooperation, Ye Liansong suggested that overall
planning for industrial structure and layout, and for capital
construction projects such as those for airports and expressways,
should be worked out.
</P>
<P>
He added that cooperation between enterprises should be
promoted and large enterprise groups formed to jointly develop
resources.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested the establishment of a market system to
promote exchanges of talents and information, and increase of
cooperation in utilization of water sources and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
Ye pointed out cooperation will mainly be conducted among
enterprises, and the government, while rendering support, will
focus on infrastructure and some large projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
