<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Development For North China Discussed (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- High ranking officials from north
China's Beijing and Tianjin municipalities, and Hebei province,
will increase their cooperation to promote economic prosperity for
the Bohai Bay rim and the whole of northern China.
</P>
<P>
The two mayors and the provincial governor held discussions on
how to achieve common development while attending the ongoing
session of the National People's Congress (NPC) here.
</P>
<P>
According to China's development program for the next 15 years,
which is being examined at the current NPC session, the Bohai Bay
rim along China's east coastline is one of the seven
trans-provincial economic zones. Beijing, Tianjin and Hebei, along
with two peninsulas around the bay, constitute the main body of
the zone.
</P>
<P>
Ye Liansong, governor of Hebei province, said the Bohai Bay rim
will become the third engine for China's economic take-off by the
end of this century, after the Pearl River delta in south China
and the Yangtze River delta supported by an economic belt along
the river.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Mayor Zhang Lichang expected the rim to bring along
economic prosperity in northern China, as well as connect the
north with the south.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Mayor Li Qiyan expressed Beijing's wish to join in the
regional economy, which will promote the whole region's as well as
the city's economic expansion.
</P>
<P>
The officials said that the tripartite economic cooperation
will play a key role in the formation of the Bohai Bay rim
economic zone.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
