<HEADLINE> Sanya-Macao Air Route Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Sanya City in south China's Hainan
province had its first chartered flight to Macao today.
</P>
<P>
The flight signals the inauguration of the 700-km air route,
which has a flying time of one hour and 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
More such flights are scheduled for March 18 and April.
</P>
<P>
A series of domestic and international air routes have been
opened since Fenghuang International Airport began operating.
</P>
<P>
With the approval from the CAAC, eight flights from Sanya to
Singapore, Malaysia, Japan, Thailand, Germany, the Republic of
Korea, Hong Kong, and Macao will start within the year, according
to one source.
</P>
<P>
Four of these flights will be changed from unscheduled
chartered flights to regular ones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
