<HEADLINE> Saddened Cricket Fan Commits Suicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- An Indian cricket fan committed
suicide in the eastern state of West Bengal after India was
announced the loser to Sri Lanka following a crowd vilolence on
Wednesday's World Cup semi-final at Calcutta, reports said here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ashoke Roy, 35, hanged himself in front of his television set
in the West Bengal town of Debnagar moments after violence erupted
following an Indian batting collapse at Calcutta's Eden Gardens.
</P>
<P>
The match was then awarded to Sri Lanka, who will play in the
final at Lahore on Sunday. 
</P>
