<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Military Launches Search Operation In East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 14 (Xinhua)-- A massive search operation is now
under way in Trincomlee's Naval Dockyard Complex in the east by
Sri Lankan army, navy and police units who are hunting for a Tamil
rebel suicide squad, according to defense sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said some 3,000 military personnel are involved in
the operation which was launched after the security authorities
received reports that a group of unidentified men had infiltrated
a navy facility last night.
</P>
<P>
They added that the search was under way and the 500-acre
complex has been surrounded by the military personnel.
</P>
<P>
Rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) launched
suicide attacks in April last year destroying two navy gunboats
and killing 12 Navy personnel in the Trincomlee harbor waters near
the navy dockyard.
</P>
<P>
That attack also marked the LTTE rebels' resolve to end the
peace talks with the government, which were held in Jaffna city.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE, which has been fighting against the government for a
separate Tamil state since 1983, has conducted several devastating
bomb blasts in Colombo during the last three months, after the
government troops mounted military attacks on LTTE bases in the
northern Jaffna peninsula and recaptured the rebel stronghold
Jaffna city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
