<HEADLINE> Hangzhou High-Speed Paging Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Hangzhou, capital city of east
China's Zhejiang Province, has opened two high-speed pager
networks using Motorola's technology.
</P>
<P>
The two networks, with a total investment of 18 million yuan
(2.17 million US dollars) from the city's telecommunications
bureau, cover the downtown area and seven counties.
</P>
<P>
They used Motorola's FLEX to double paging capacity and speed,
and incorporate 23 basic stations, according to the People's Posts
and Telecommunications Daily.
</P>
<P>
Satellite-based global positioning system technology is also
used for the city's high-speed paging system, the paper said.
</P>
</TEXT>
