<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns U.S. Interference in China's Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Iran today strongly condemned
U.S. interference in China's internal affairs, saying the United
States has no business in the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio said in its commentary today that
the U.S. is "trying to internationalize the conflict between
Beijing and Taipei" in the past two days.
</P>
<P>
The commentary also criticized Washington for dispatching two
aircraft carriers to the region, terming it a "blatant form of
terrorism."
</P>
<P>
"The provocative actions by the U.S. has created a crisis in
the region, especially in the Straits of Taiwan," the commentary
said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the U.S. was motivated by "its own hegemonic
aims" in confronting China as "one of the world's atomic powers
and a member of the Security Council." 
</P>
</TEXT>
