<HEADLINE> Inter-Korean Trade Exceeds 1 Billion Dollars Since 1989 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Cumulative trade between South
Korea and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) between
1989 and 1995 exceeded 1 billion U.S. dollars, according to the
National Unification Board (NUB).
</P>
<P>
As of the end of 1995, the value of inter-Korean trade,
beginning in 1989, stood at 1.22 billion dollars on an approved
basis and 990 million dollars on a customs cleared basis, said a
report issued by the NUB today.
</P>
<P>
If South Korea's 150,000-ton rice shipment to the DPRK last
year is included, the figures will increase to 1.43 billion
dollars and 1.22 billion dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
South Korea suffered a 770-million-dollar deficit in trade with
the DPRK during the seven-year period.
</P>
<P>
Direct trade accounted for only 5.3 percent of inter-Korean
trade, which was conducted mostly via third countries, the report
added. 
</P>
