<HEADLINE> More Farmers Escape Poverty in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of young peasants in
central China have not only escaped poverty, but have become
wealthy.
</P>
<P>
The rags-to-riches success of Henan province's peasants has
been attributed to various kinds of technical training courses.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up many technical service centers and
technical training bases at provincial and county levels, where
young peasants can consult, and learn practical skills.
</P>
<P>
Many have become wealthy and helped others become well-fed
after studying at the training bases.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 percent of rural youth in the province will master
at least one practical skill, over 20 percent have hopes of
getting wealthy and one million will escape poverty in the next
five years, thanks to efforts by local governments.
</P>
<P>
Henan now boasts more than 20,000 youth service organizations
and entities, which are playing a very important role in rural
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The province has 12.5 million young peasants, whose action has
an important bearing on the process of poverty-relief and
modernization in rural areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
