<HEADLINE> Jackson Wins 110 Meters Hurdles at Australian Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- World 110 meters hurdles record
holder Colin Jackson of Britain won the event at the Australian
Grand Prix athletics final in Brisbane on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Jackson, who pulled out of the 100 meters hurdles final at last
week's Australian Championships with a groin injury, clocked 13.22
seconds, only 0.13 seconds ahead of Australian champion Kyle
Vander-Kuyp, who was edged to the second place.
</P>
