<HEADLINE> Arab Foreign Ministers Meet in Cairo on Arab Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Arab Foreign ministers met here
today for the 105 session of the Arab League Council to discuss
Arab unity and Arab cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to Egypt's Middle East News Agency, the 19 foreign
ministers will discuss some 25 items on the agenda which is
related to boosting joint Arab cooperation in the political,
economic economic and financial fields.
</P>
<P>
On top of the agenda are all tracks of the peace process in the
Middle East, especially the Palestinian cause, the issues of
Jerusalem, the Palestinian refugees and development in the
Palestinian lands.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League Council session will also discuss the statute
of the Arab Court of Justice, the draft Code of Honor of Arab
security and cooperation and the setting up of a mechanism for
avoiding and settling inter-Arab conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The agenda also includes Israel's occupation of the Syria's
Golan Heights and parts of south Lebanon and western Beqaa and the
necessity of implementing relevant U.N. Security Council
resolutions besides the issues of detainees in Israeli jails.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Somalia and Iran's occupation of three UAE
islands will be also discussed.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Arab League's 105 session will discus a report
on nuclear threat in the Middle East and the need to clear the
region from weapons of mass destruction including nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
The session will also discuss the political and legal aspects
of the water resources in the light of a memo sent by Syria to the
Arab League.
</P>
<P>
The Libya-West crisis and the measures adopted against Libya
will be also discussed.
</P>
<P>
Israel's collective punishment against Palestinians after the
recent suicide bombings in the Jewish country will also be on the
agenda, MENA said. 
