<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 12:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,800-year-old Tomb in Cliff Found in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Archaeologists in southwest
China's Sichuan Province have found a 1,800-year-old large tomb
carved into a cliff.
</P>
<P>
Located 20 meters above the Yuanbao mountain foot in Santai
county, the 15.4m long tomb has a door way leading to three
chambers.
</P>
<P>
Relief sculptures can be found on the ceiling, walls and
pillars of the tomb.
</P>
<P>
From the inscriptions of "Yong He" (in Chinese meaning
permanent peace), the experts concluded that the tomb was built
during the years of Yong He (136-141) in the Eastern Han Dynasty
(25-220).
</P>
<P>
No cultural relics remained, except for some pottery that is
frequently seen in Eastern Han tombs.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that although the tomb had at some stage been
robbed, it will still contribute to the study of burial systems of
the dynasty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 12:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jilin Farmers Turn Courtyards into Pay-Dirt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Traditional courtyards have
become a money spinner for farmers in northeast China's Jilin
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Statistics Bureau reports that in 1995 farmers
earned 4.6 billion yuan from what they described as "courtyard
economy," which includes planting cash crops and trees, raising
domestic animals and operating workshops.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented a 25 percent increase from 1994, an
official of the bureau said, adding that 68 percent of the rural
households each earned at least 1,800 yuan from the economy last
year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, the provincial government in the major grain
producing area has been encouraging farmers to become prosperous
by boosting the courtyard economy.
</P>
<P>
In 1995 about 2.5 million rural households, 75 percent of the
province's total, participated in a competition held to expand the
courtyard economy. The acreage of their courtyards amounted to
138,500 hectares, 81 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Last year agro-technicians held training courses for four
million farmers, spreading knowledge about 100 new techniques in
rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
