<HEADLINE> Nine Players to Leave Swedish Champions Club </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Nine players in Swedish
champions IFK Gothenburg, with their contract still in force, are
set to move abroad following the Bosman case on the free movement
of footballers in Europe, reports said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The group, which includes World Cup midfielder Jesper Blomqvist
and six other internationals, said they are exercising the right
to tear up their contracts.
</P>
<P>
The Bosman ruling by the European Court of Justice last
December stipulated that European Union clubs can field as many
E.U. nationals as they wish.
</P>
<P>
The ruling also abolished transfer fees on players who are out
of contract. 
</P>
