<HEADLINE> Xishuangbanna Airport to Open to Overseas Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUNMING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Jinghong Airport, which serves the
famous scenic spot of Xishuangbanna in southwest China's Yunnan
province, is expected to open to overseas flights next month.
</P>
<P>
The provincial port administration authorities announced that
the State Council, China's highest governing body, has approved
the opening of the airport, situated in Jinghong city of the
Dai-inhabited Xishuangbanna prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Bordering Burma and Laos, Xishuangbanna is well-known for its
spectacular tropical landscape and unique culture of ethnic
minorities. It draws thousands of overseas travellers each year.
</P>
<P>
Jinghong Airport, which officially went into operation in April,
1994, is capable of accommodating Boeing 737-300 planes and
freighters.
</P>
<P>
So far, expansion of the airport and building of complementary
facilities have been completed.
</P>
<P>
The airport is scheduled to open in mid-April, on the eve of the
water-splashing festival, New Year holiday of the Dai ethnic
minorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
