<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 11:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Trade Deficit Reaches 45.97 Million US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Macao's trade deficit in 1995
reached 354 million Patacas (about 45.97 million US dollars), down
82.9 percent from that in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics released by the Macao Statistics and Census
Department show that the imports in 1995 totaled 16.3 billion
Patacas (about 2.12 billion US dollars), down 3.9 percentage points
from that in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The value of exports topped 15.9 billion Patacas (about 2.06
billion US dollars), up 7.1 percent from that in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Most of the export items of Macao were textile products, garments
and toys, while imports range from food, fuel, daily use articles to
electronics products, among others.
</P>
<P>
The exports to the European Union added up to five billion
Patacas (about 649.35 million US dollars), accounting for 31.7
percent of all exports. It was also a 4.3 percent increase from that
of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The largest export market remained to be the United States,
which imported 42.1 percent of all exports of Macao, compared with
37.2 percent in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The main import market for Macao was the Asia-Pacific region,
including Hong Kong, Republic of Korea, Japan, China's mainland and
Taiwan. Other import markets include the United States and the
European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0133 </DOCNO>
