<HEADLINE> Spain Nips Czech Republic in Olympic Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Reigning Olympic soccer champion
Spain defeated Czech Republic 2-1 in the first leg of the
qualifying match for the 1994 Games in Granada, Spain, Wednesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
Spain took a halftime lead 2-0 through goals from Roberto
Fresnedero in the 28th minute and Dani Garcia four minutes before
the break.
</P>
<P>
The Czechs scored a precious goal in the fifth minute of the
second half.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the tie qualifies for the Olympics while the
loser must hope to go through as the best of the five runners-up.
</P>
