<HEADLINE> Canadian-Chinese Donates For China's Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A Canadian-Chinese businessman
has donated 10 million yuan's worth-of computers to a university
and a middle school in southwest China's Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony to mark the donations was held in the Great Hall of
the People in the Chinese capital three days ago.
</P>
<P>
Wang Dongfang, vice-president of the ONYX Computer Company and
vice-president of the Canadian International Film and Television
Corporation, has donated computer systems totalling 45 million
yuan to the Zhongshan University in south China's Guangdong
province and a middle school in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Wang said at the ceremony that he will set up a primary school
in Sichuan province to mark the 60th anniversary of the victory of
the Long March.
</P>
<P>
The Long March, a strategic movement of the Chinese Workers'
and Peasants' Red Army, succeeded in reaching the revolutionary
base in northern Shaanxi covering 12,500 km, 1934-1935.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan is one of the eleven provinces which the Red Army
traversed. 
