<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stock Market Rebounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on Hong Kong's
stock market rebounded with Hang Seng Index rising 202 points to
10,451.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time for the share prices to rebound this week
after two tumbles at the local bourse Monday and Wednesday when
Hang Seng Index dropped 820 and 352 points respectively due to the
plummeting of the stocks in New York and London.
</P>
<P>
All Hang Seng sectoral sub-indices climbed up today with
finance up 264 points to 9,987, utilities rising 206.84 points to
10,376, properties climbing 335 points to 18,807 and commercials
and industrials increasing 107.82 points to 7,760.
</P>
<P>
Today's Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and MidCap 50 Index
rose 5.8 and 19.05 points to 832.54 and 1,336.94 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Stock experts said that today's rebounding is under expectation
and the general situation on Hong Kong Stock Market is good.
</P>
<P>
But, they noted, the down-and-up trend will last for some time
on the market due to various factors on the overseas market.
</P>
</TEXT>
