<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 11:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Criticizes US Over Wheat Quarantine Issue (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the following decade and more, the US government made no
reference to China to the sale of infected wheat.
</P>
<P>
However, since the beginning of the 1990s, the US side brought
up this issue again, saying that "the TCK occurrence actually is
not suited to the natural conditions of China," except for very
few places.
</P>
<P>
In view of this, the US urged China to open all ports south to
Dalian city to wheat exported from US TCK-infected areas.
</P>
<P>
The request was rejected by China once again.
</P>
<P>
Frustrated by China's hard stance, the US side has altered its
tactics since last year, labeling the TCK dispute as "a political
issue" instead of a "technical problem."
</P>
<P>
Taking the refusal of China as one technical barrier affecting
bilateral trade, the US began to relate the dispute with China's
reentry of the GATT ad entry of the WTO, coercing China to make a
"political decision".
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the US side incited dozens of Congressmen who were
unaware of the truth to write letters to Chinese leaders, aiming
at exerting more pressure on China.
</P>
<P>
Officials in charge of the two government organs stressed in
the Chinese capital that the production safety of wheat, a staple
food for China, a big agricultural country with over 1.2 billion
people, is extremely important.
</P>
<P>
As a quarantine policy, China's ban on imports of wheat from
TCK infected areas is based on results of a number of scientific
appraisals, and fully conforms to the international practice.
</P>
<P>
While banning wheat import from US TCK-infected areas, they
noted, China permits no import of such crop from any country and
region with TCK occurrence. The quarantine policy is on no account
such a "technical barrier" as the US side described.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side holds to the belief that the TCK dispute is a
sheer technical issue, which should be settled through technical
co-operation of the two sides, they said.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to seek the solution to this problem through a
bilateral technical co-operation, which is based on a shared
respect for science, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
