the past few years. Bilateral trade volume stood at 30 million US
dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Romania exports mainly metallurgical goods and chemical
products to Malaysia, while Malaysia exports mainly natural
rubber, cocoa and its products, and electrical components to
Romania.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is rich in good-quality wood, while Romania is good at
furniture manufacturing, Ion said. The two countries should take
the advantage of these attractive conditions and also these
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
