<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 10:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Criticizes US Over Wheat Quarantine Issue (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- China today accused the United
States of adopting double standards on wheat quarantine "for its
own interests". It criticized the US for what it described as a
hegemonic act.
</P>
<P>
Officials with China's Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC) and State Administration for Quarantine of
Animals and Plants, said that on December 20 last year, 12 US
congressmen from five wheat production states jointly wrote to the
Clinton Administration, asking for US talks with Mexico on wheat
to be slowed down, due to the issue of Karnal bunt of wheat.
</P>
<P>
The US Government decided, as a result, to postpone its
importation of wheat from Mexico.
</P>
<P>
However, on December 12 last year, 30 US congressmen from wheat
production states jointly wrote to Chinese leaders, criticizing
China's quarantine of the Tilletia Controversa Kuhu (TCK) as
unscientific.
</P>
<P>
They asked China to amend quarantine laws and regulations to
permit TCK-infected wheat from the US to enter China, and imposed
pressure on China repeatedly, in the name of this "political
issue".
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the US side put China on the "super 301 list for
observation" last year for a so-called limitation of US products
with unfair trade barriers.
</P>
<P>
The officials noted that this act by the US should be condemned.
</P>
<P>
The officials said that the TCK will exert great harm on the
production of wheat, adding it was even much more dangerous than
the Karnal bunt. They added it is very difficult to prevent, cure
and wipe out the TCK.
</P>
<P>
At present, many countries and organizations in the world have
listed the TCK on namelists for quarantine, including 36 members
of the European and Mediterranean Plant Protection Organization
(EPPO), as well as Australia, Canada and the IAPPC.
</P>
<P>
The officials said that the Chinese Government has always
treated the TCK issue scientifically, while not completely
forbidding the import of US wheat simply because some areas of the
US were infected by the TCK.
</P>
<P>
They added that as early as the early 1970s when China started
to import US wheat, China found out the TCK existing in some areas
of the US during quarantine.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning, the US side did not admit the fact, and they
had to admit it when Chinese experts presented evidence obtained
from the US wheat exported to China, said the Chinese officials.
</P>
<P>
After that, the US side spread the view that "TCK infection is
not harmful", which was refuted by the Chinese side, the officials
pointed out.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0153 </DOCNO>
