<HEADLINE> Dial-a-meal service in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A dial-a-veg service in China's
port city of Tianjin is mushrooming. For subscribers the days of
standing in queues at markets are over. Instead they just pick up
the phone and a supply of fresh vegetables are sent to their homes.
</P>
<P>
The family vegetable transportation service, offered by the
Tianjin Enzhe Public Secretarial Service Company, has become so
popular among local residents that it is growing by 30 customers a
day.
</P>
<P>
Customers each pay 310 yuan(37 US dollars) a month for 60
dishes of vegetables or meat, which are washed, cut, and made, up
by a team of cooks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
