<HEADLINE> SAARC Inter-Governmental Group Meets In Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 14 (Xinhua)-- A meeting of the
inter-governmental group on trade liberalization (LGG) to initiate
the second round of trade negotiations under the South Asia
Preferential Trading Arrangement (SAPTA) was held here today.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials from the trade ministries of the seven SAPTA
contracting states attended the meeting which was inaugurated by
Kingsley Wickremaratne, Sri Lankan minister of trade, commerce and
food.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting will consider working out modalities for
removal of para-tariff, non-tariff and other trade control
barriers within a specified time frame, according to conference
sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the meeting will adopt a negotiating
approach for the second round of negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The LGG meeting will also consider further measures for trade
facilitation among the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation (SAARC) countries such as improving the procedures for
the granting of visa for the business travel among the SAARC
countries, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC, founded in 1985, groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India,
the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 09:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Work Starts on China's First SDH Microwave Cable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The construction of China's first
SDH (synchronous digital hierarchy) microwave trunk was kicked off
March 2.
</P>
<P>
The project will connect the digital telecommunications
networks of Wuchang, a district of Wuhan city, and Fuzhou, capital
of Fujian Province, according to the journal "People's Posts and
Telecommunications".
</P>
<P>
The 796-km-long microwave line has adopted the SDH equipment of
the Canada-based North Telecom Company, and will have 19 microwave
relay stations.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that this will be a new telecommunications
artery in booming south China, and will promote the expansion
of other microwave trunks nearby. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
