<HEADLINE> Mother of 10th Panchen Lama Celebrates 80th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held in Beijing on
Wednesday to mark the 80th birthday of Soinam Zholma, mother of
the late tenth Panchen Lama.
</P>
<P>
Soinam Zholma, a member of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), was in
the capital to attend the Fourth Plenary Session of the Eighth
CPPCC National Committee which closed yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yandong, deputy head of the United Front Work Department of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
presented Soinam Zholma with a basket of flowers, and wished her
good health and long life.
</P>
<P>
Soinam Zholma, who is also vice-chairperson of the Tibet
Autonomous Regional Committee of the CPPCC, thanked the Chinese
Communist Party and the government for always taking good care of
her.
</P>
<P>
"The tenth Panchen Lama was not only a leader of Tibetan
Buddism, but also a sincere friend of the CPC, and a patriot
upholding China's reunification cause, and firmly opposing
splittism," she said.
</P>
<P>
The soul boy of the late 10th Panchen Lama has been enthroned
following the drawing of lots from a gold urn and State Council
approval.
</P>
<P>
She added that she had paid respect to the eleventh Panchen
Lama a few days ago.
</P>
<P>
She expressed the hope that the new Panchen Lama will carry
forward the behests of the late Panchen Lama, study Buddhist
scriptures diligently, love the motherland, be devoted to the
religion, and contribute to unity among various ethnic groups, and
China's reunification.  
</P>
</TEXT>
