<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Enrol More College Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- About 965,000 new students will
be recruited by Chinese universities and colleges this autumn,
39,000 more than last year's enrollment number.
</P>
<P>
About half of this year's high school graduates across the
country will be able to enter 1,054 universities and colleges for
advanced studies, according to a national conference on university
enrollment which closed in Nanjing, capital city of Jiangsu
Province today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, over 1,100 adult colleges, which provide higher
education and professional training programs for employees, are to
enrol 860,000 people this year, a rise of 25,000 over the number
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Enrollment work will be started after the annual national adult
college entrance examinations in May and college entrance
examinations in July.
</P>
<P>
The number of college students in China has increased steadily
in the past five years, since the government took measures to
develop higher education, the State Education Commission said.
</P>
<P>
There are about 2.8 million students in China's colleges and
universities. The total number will increase to 6.3 million by the
year of 2000, according to a plan for development of higher
education in the next five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
