<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 08:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hubei Promotes Social Security System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province has
established a unified social security system covering retirement
pensions, unemployment insurance, workmen's compensation
childbirth insurance and medical coverage.
</P>
<P>
Retirement pensions are the focal point. By the end of last
year, 2.88 million people, including 530,000 retired workers, well
over 90 percent of the total staff of local state enterprises were
part of retirement pension schemes.
</P>
<P>
This pension coverage has been extended to all types of
workers, not just state employees. To date, some 470,000 employees
of collective, joint-stock and private businesses have
participated the retirement pension insurance.
</P>
<P>
There are 3.53 million people in 24,728 local enterprises of
all types in Hubei registered with the unemployment insurance
scheme, and 60,000 among them are covered by the insurance.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province has set a social security system of
workmen's compensation and medical insurance in its 85 cities and
counties.
</P>
<P>
More than 1.12 million women workers in 49 cities and counties
in the province have registered with the childbirth insurance
scheme, and there are reportedly some 9,683 women workers in 49
cities and counties covered by the scheme.
</P>
<P>
To further promote the social security system, the local
government has helped 3.4 million employees set up insurance
accounts province-wide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
