<HEADLINE> Hangzhou to Build "Charity Town" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Hangzhou Charity Society in
this capital of east China's Zhejiang Province plans to build a
"charity town" covering an area of 1.2 ha.
</P>
<P>
The town will provide a haven for the poor elderly people and
disabled children. There will consist of 6,000 sq m of apartments
for the elderly, a 1,000-sq-m hospital, a 2,000-sq-m
rehabilitation center for children and a 1,000-sq-m administration
center.
</P>
<P>
The charity society, established by local enterprises,
sponsored dozens of medical operations for disabled children in
1995.
</P>
<P>
It will use donations from all sources to build the city, which
will install telephone hot-lines and provide emergency and special
help services. 
