<HEADLINE> Martinez Sails into Evert Cup Semi-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Conchita Martinez
beat American Lindsay Lee in straight sets to coast into the
semi-final of the Evert Cup women's tennis tournament in Indian
Wells, California, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The quarter-final match, which was delayed three hours because
of the rain, saw Lee opened the first set with a 4-2 lead over
Martinez.
</P>
<P>
But Martinez rallied to win the set 7-5 and never looked back
in the second set, which she took 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Martinez now faces a semi-final clash with Japanese Kimiko
Date, who came from one set down to beat France's Nathalie Tauziat
6-7 (2-7), 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In another quarter-final, American Lindsay Davenport upset
compatriot Chanda Rubin 6-0, 6-3 to meet world co-number one
Steffi Graf.
</P>
<P>
Rubin, who crumbled under Davenport's attacks, was never in the
form that brought her the 6-3, 6-3 victory over Jennifer Capriati
of the United States on Tuesday. 
</P>
