<HEADLINE> Five More Bandits Killed In Northern Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan combined force of
security personnel on Wednesday killed five more "bandits" in
Marsabit District, northern Kenya, following Saturday's a fierce
battle in which 25 bandits were killed.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 bandits suspected to be Ethiopians crossed the
boarder to Dukana, North Horr in Kenya last week, where they
attacked herdsmen and killed 13 people in a village in Marsabit
District, "Kenya Times" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Eastern Provincial Commissioner (PC) Ismael
Chelang'a confirmed the incident. He told the paper that security
had been beefed up to counter further attacks and to pursue the
bandits who were driving away some 120 heads of cattle.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Commissioner urged the Kenyan families affected
by the attack to remain calm as the government is tracking down
the attackers with a view to arresting them.
</P>
<P>
By last night, the security had been still pursuing the bandits
believed to have crossed the Kenya border from Ethiopian and
suspected to be from Amarkoke in the neighboring country.
</P>
</TEXT>
