<HEADLINE> Souvenir Badges Commemorating Sun Yat-sen in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
recently issued a set of two badges in its capital of Nanjing to
mark the 130th anniversary of the birth of Dr. Sun Yat-sen.
</P>
<P>
The souvenir badges feature a portrait of Dr. Sun Yat-sen in
1912 when he was provisional president after the last Chinese
dynasty had been overthrown. An inscription in Chinese and English
which announces the "130th Anniversary of the Birth of Dr. Sun
Yat-sen" and a picture of the Provisional President's Palace
located in Nanjing appear on the two sides of the badges.
</P>
<P>
The badges are gold- and silver-plated, and have a diameter of
40 mm and 27 mm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
