<HEADLINE> Mugabe On Indigenization Of Zimbabwe's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The indigenization of the
country's economy will be a key objective for the Zimbabwean
government to enable the people to be completely sovereign,
President Robert Mugabe has said.
</P>
<P>
In a TV broadcast last night, Mugabe said black people must be
substantially involved in all areas of the economy from
agriculture, commerce and industry to mining. There should be
others to work along with blacks in the economy but these should
only serve to reinforce Zimbabweans who will be the main
operators.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe said foreign-owned companies will be encouraged to
open up to Zimbabweans in the interests of peace and development.
</P>
<P>
The ownership of land must also be indigenized and the land
question must now be settled ''once and for all'', he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the people of Zimbabwe must continue to be
united at various levels of society to foster development.
</P>
</TEXT>
