<HEADLINE> Afghan Refugees to Leave Iran for Homeland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Some 250,000 Afghan refugees in
Iran will leave for home via Turkmenistan next month, an official
report said here today.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that these refugees
would return to Afghanistan's northern and central provinces.
</P>
<P>
Ahmad Husseini, Director-General for Expatriate and Refugee
Affairs at the Interior Ministry, said that the voluntary return
program of Afghan refugees is based on the trilateral agreement
signed between Iran, Afghanistan and Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan refugees willing to return home should apply at
governorate offices throughout the country from next April, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that 25 U.S. dollars plus a carpet and a 50-kg wheat
bag will be given to every Afghan refugee who leaves Iran within
the program.
</P>
<P>
Husseini said that some 500,000 Afghan refugees should return
to their homeland in 1995, but because of intensification of the
Afghan civil war, only 120,000 refugees could leave Iran.
</P>
<P>
He also said that at present about 2 million Afghan
refugees are living in Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
