<HEADLINE> Rebels Ambush Bus In North Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Rebel Lord's Resistance Army
(LRA) ambushed a Kampala bound minibus from Arua in North Uganda,
killing an unspecified number of people on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today said the bus was attacked by the
rebels when it was approaching a place, two kilometers to Karuma
bridge.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Mrs. Shiama Awuma, a survivor of the
incident as saying, "The bus carried about 30 people. The rebels
removed whatever they wanted and spare some of them after the
attack.
</P>
<P>
She said her husband was among the people who were killed
during the attack.
</P>
<P>
She said six of the survivors were picked up by a Red Cross
vehicle heading for Kampala from Arua.
</P>
<P>
She said four of the survivors including herself were unhurt.
</P>
<P>
"The dead and the vehicle were left at the scene of the
attack," she added.
</P>
<P>
This is the second attack within a week by the rebels on
civilian vehicles plying the Karuma-Pakwach route.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday the rebels attacked a 17-vehicle convoy, killing
an estimated 70 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
