<HEADLINE> Shanghai Market Brisk in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A record 10.53 billion yuan was
earned last month in Shanghai from retailing consumer goods, a rise
of 44.8 percent compared with the same period of 1995, allowing
for inflation.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time for this largest city in China to top
10 billion yuan in turnover from retail in a month.
</P>
<P>
The retail sales volume in local urban and rural areas rose
57.8 percent and 46.8 percent, respectively, over the same period
of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The city earned 5.023 billion yuan from selling foodstuffs,
accounting for nearly half the city's total volume from retail
sales, a net increase of 44.1 percent compared to the same 1995
period.
</P>
<P>
Sales of garments rose 65.4 percent to 4.5 million pieces in
February, with cashmere items selling particularly well.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, nearly 70 million yuan was earned from selling
jewelry, an increase of 36.8 percent over the same period of
1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
