<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Chinese Farmer's Legendary Tale on Ecological Farming  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Proceeding from the specific conditions of his village, Zhang
tried to grope about for "biological energy"-- something that he
was unaware of at that time.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said: "We put human droppings into pits to produce biogas
for use in lighting and cooking. Then we put the dregs and
residues into fish pools and move the pool silts to the farmland."
</P>
<P>
"So there comes a fine cycle between such waste materials and
energy," Zhang explained.
</P>
<P>
"In the early days when I was the village head, my villagers
wished to have porridge and then steamed dumplings, and afterwards
wanted to live in tile-roofed houses, and a park, a zoo as well as
a recreation center," he said.
</P>
<P>
The village now has an apple orchard, a peach yard and a garden
and reduced the amount of chemical fertilizers and pesticides, all
contributing to controlling environmental pollution, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said he even did not know what the name of "ecological
agriculture" is meant until several years ago when Qu Geping, then
head of the State Environment Agency, accompanied a deputy
secretary-general of the United Nations for an inspection tour of
his village.
</P>
<P>
Only until then did Zhang learn that he had found a solution to
ecological farming for areas of poorer countries, for which the UN
had worked and searched for decades.
</P>
<P>
According to his understanding, Zhang said, ecological farming
is to plant more trees, grow more flowers and grass, curb soil
erosion, planning on birth of babies, and longer life span for the
elderly.
</P>
<P>
The average life expectancy in Xiaozhangzhuang has reached 74
for male and 77 for female, exceeding the national average,
Zhang noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that his village has set up kindergartens, schools and
libraries in the recent years. Primary education has been
popularized and 30 percent of the villagers have received
secondary or higher education.
</P>
<P>
"Xiaozhangzhuang has created a model in getting rid of poverty
through improvement of ecological conditions and development of
ecological farming," said Qu Geping, now chairman of the
Environment and Resources Protection Committee of the National
People's Congress.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
