<HEADLINE> HK Urban Council Delegation to Visit US, Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Urban Council of Hong Kong
has sent a delegation on a 10-day visit to three cities in the
United States and Canada this week, a spokesman of the council
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The six-member delegation is to learn about the latest
developments in a wide range of municipal services in Los Angeles,
San Francisco and Vancouver.
</P>
<P>
The Urban Council is one of the statutory authorities in Hong
Kong in charge of the services like street cleaning, refuse
collection and public facilities management.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the fact-finding visit from March 14 to
23 will cover methods of running arts and culture facilities, the
operation of a central library, application of information
technology in upgrading city services, management of stadium,
liquor licensing polices, and efficient waste-disposal practices
with a focus on operation of modern waste incinerators.
</P>
<P>
The first stop of the delegation is Los Angeles, where topping
the list of its packed schedule will be a visit to the University
of California Film and Television Archive, the world's largest
university collection of motion pictures and broadcast
programming, and the Academy Film Archive in Beverly Hills.
</P>
<P>
The visits are for the planning for the Hong Kong Film Archive
to be built at Sai Wan Ho, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In Los Angeles, the delegation will also visit the Department
of Alcoholic and Beverage Control, Museum of Contemporary Art of
Los Angeles and the City of Commerce-Refuse-to-Energy Plant.
</P>
<P>
In San Francisco on March 19, the delegation will visit the
city's War Memorial and Performing Arts Center, Museum of Modern
Art, Sunset Scavenger Company and State Food and Drug Branch.
</P>
<P>
In Vancouver, Canada, the delegation will see the operations of
the Vancouver Central Library and the B.C. Place Stadium.
</P>
</TEXT>
