<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Develops Hi-Tech Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province is making great efforts to develop
hi-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Work is now underway on the second phase of the Guangzhou
Tianhe Hi-Tech Industrial Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
As many as 1,200 enterprises have been set up in the zone, 25
of which are export-oriented ones, and more than 1,000 of which
are non-governmental.
</P>
<P>
Of the total 120 hi-tech enterprises recognized by the city,
104 are situated in the zone.
</P>
<P>
Last year the zone generated a total income of three billion
yuan from industry and trade, and earned more than 16 million US
dollars in foreign exchange from exports.
</P>
<P>
The city is now striving to put even more effort into building
up its successful development zones in a bid to use high
technology industries to promote city development. 
</P>
