<HEADLINE> ADB to Study Law Institutions in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
has approved a technical assistance of 600,000 US dollars to
examine the role of law and legal institutions in Asia's economic
development, reports said here today.
</P>
<P>
The assistance will be used to investigate economic laws, legal
institutions and legal professions in selected Asian economies
during the period of 1960-95.
</P>
<P>
The study will examine law reform process and its relations to
the economic and social changes during the period. It will also
evaluate the impact of foreign legal models.
</P>
<P>
The study aims to draw lessons from the experience to provide
guidance for the bank's developing member countries in future
legal system reforms and to help the bank shape future assistance
in support of such reforms.  
</P>
</TEXT>
