<HEADLINE> Peace, Not Terrorism in Middle East: Menem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem today hoped that the current summit of peace in Egypt will
be conducive to the peace process in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, Menem said
that he is aware of the historical significance of the Sharm el
Sheij meeting and of the fact that it is being held under
difficult circumstances.
</P>
<P>
Menem also sent his government's rejection of terrorism in all
forms.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Argentine government has pronounced in a clear
and irrevocable way that the country is in favor of the peace
negotiations in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine president said that his government welcomed the
agreements reached so far because they constitute the only
possible alternative for reaching and guaranteeing the well-being
of the people in the region.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from 30 countries drafted today in Sharm el Sheij a
document calling for peace and condemning all forms of terrorism
during the opening ceremony of the summit. 
