<HEADLINE> Storm Leaves One Dead, Hundreds Homeless in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 13 (Xinhua) -- At least one person
died, hundreds were left homeless and major damage was
caused by a storm in northern Argentina, authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
Authorities in Rosario said that with one person dead and 300
homeless, the storm was the worst to strike their city in a
decade.
</P>
<P>
The storm left Rosario without electricity and drinking water
on Wednesday and in Resistencia, rooftops were blown away, power
cables brought down and trees uprooted.
</P>
<P>
Cordoba reported flooding and interruption of electricity
supplies as hundreds of people had to abandon their homes in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The storm also caused flooding elsewhere and damaged cotton,
soya and sunflower crops which were about to be harvested.
</P>
</TEXT>
