<HEADLINE> Dhaka Opposition Reiterates Cancellation of Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Immediate cancellation of the
ruling party-held "farcical" February polls is the only way to
solve Bangladesh's political crisis, opposition parties have
reiterated.
</P>
<P>
The firm stand was stated Wednesday in their separate letters,
almost identical, in response to the president's call for putting
forward their respective suggestions on the framework of the
proposed caretaker government for holding general elections
following their earlier discussions with the president.
</P>
<P>
On March 10-11, President Abdur Rahman Biswas held separate
meetings with the opposition parties and the ruling Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) in his initiative for resolution to the
national crisis through dialogues.
</P>
<P>
In the letters, the mainstream opposition parties led by the
Awami (People's) League expressed their doubts about a positive
outcome of the presidential move as "the February polls is yet to
be declared null and void and the cabinet headed by Begum Khaleda
Zia still to resign."
</P>
<P>
Without that, there is little scope for any effective step
towards the formation of a non-party caretaker government, the
opposition parties said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing their willingness to cooperate with the president
in ending the persisting political crisis, the opposition parties
hoped that the president would pave the way for resolving the
problem by ensuring immediate cancellation of the February
elections and resignation of the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
It was learnt that the ruling BNP may communicate its proposal
to the president today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
