<HEADLINE> Date Books Semifinal Berth in Evert Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Kimiko Date survived a
first-set defeat to down France's Nathalie Tauziat on Wednesday
for her semifinal spot in the Evert Cup women's tennis in Indian
Wells, California.
</P>
<P>
In the rain-interrupted match, Fourth-seeded Date, rallied back
to beat Tauziat 6-7 (2/7), 6-3, 6-3 in one hour and 47 minutes to
join Steffi Graf in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, Tauziat managed to keep Date in the backcourt
with topspin balls and won the tiebreaker to her relief.
</P>
<P>
Date won the first three games in the second set by breaking
Tauziat in the second, before her French opponent rallied back for
the following three games in a row.
</P>
<P>
From the 3-3 tie, Date spared no efforts in the court by taking
three more games to split the first two sets.
</P>
<P>
In the decider set, Date kept her momentum going on to win the
final four games to seal the competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
