<HEADLINE> Guangxi Overseas Market Connection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, 14 (Xinhua) -- Guangxi, a multi-ethnic autonomous
region in south China, has successfully established a foothold in
overseas markets during the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The region signed 259 labor and project agreements involving
460 million US dollars and sent 4,400 technicians and workers to
work on projects abroad during 1991-95.
</P>
<P>
It has also set up 25 businesses overseas, involving 16
million US dollars of contractual investment.
</P>
<P>
In addition to being involved in the traditional markets of
Africa and South Asia, Guangxi has opened or expanded markets in
Oceania and South America.
</P>
<P>
The type of cooperation ranges from trade and investment to
exporting labor, construction, and technical service.  
</P>
</TEXT>
