<HEADLINE> Suit Filed Against King Over Alleged Match-rigging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A lawsuit has been brought
against boxing promoter Don King, boxers Julio Cesar Chavez and
Craig Houk over alleged match fixing, a Chicago newspaper reported
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chicago Sun-Times said the lawsuit filed by fight promoter
Jose Venzor alleged the Chavez-Houk bout in Chicago last July was
fixed beforehand by the trio.
</P>
<P>
Mexican Chavez needed only 79 seconds to knock out Houk in the
first round of that match.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said Venzor claimed they had defrauded him of
"hundreds of thousands of dollars."
</P>
<P>
Venzor sued Chavez in 1993 after Chavez failed to show up for a
fight he helped promote, forcing the cancellation of the bout.
