<HEADLINE> Indian Fans Riot at World Cup Cricket Semi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Indian fans rioted during a
World Cup cricket semi-final in Calcutta on Wednesday, forcing
match officials to stop the game.
</P>
<P>
Some of the 110,000 spectators began to throw objects into the
the pitch and light small fires in the stand when India slumped to
120 for eight against Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka and Indian players had to be escorted out the stadium
by the riot police and referee Clive Lloyd later awarded the game
to Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka will now play the winners of Thursday's game between
Australia and the West Indies. 
