further without hitting a single shot when his Spaniard opponent
Alex Corretja withdrew due to an ankle injury.
</P>
<P>
Andre Agassi led Sjeng Schalken of the Netherlands 6-1, 1-0
before rain interrupted the game.
</P>
<P>
Edberg, nowsdays dropped to 55th in the world rankings, was to
retire after the season of the year. He has bagged two Wimbledon
titles, two U.S. Opens and two Australian Opens. 
