<HEADLINE> Austria's New Government Sets Priorities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Employment, budget reform,
national security and the European Union will be the top
priorities for the new coalition government over the next four
years, Austrian Federal Chancellor Franz Vranitzky announced on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a 50-page statement, Vranitzky said it is not wise for a
small nation like Austria to tie itself to a certain security
system or to give up any flexibility in its security policy,
because a common security policy for Europe is still a long way
off. He pledged Austria will play an active role in world
security efforts.
</P>
<P>
On Austria's role in the EU, Vranitzky said, as an EU member,
the question for Austria is not to answer "yes" or "no" to the
European Union but to think wholeheartedly about how to build
Europe in the future.
</P>
<P>
In his statement, Vranitzky repeatedly stressed the importance
of cooperation between the Social Democratic Party and the
People's Party, the two partners in the new coalition cabinet,
which was sworn in on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chancellor also stressed the importance of good cooperation
between the government and parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian Parliament will begin to debate Vranitzky's
government statement on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
