<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Today's Economic News Briefs:
</P>
<P>
New Joint Venture
</P>
<P>
A joint venture between the Matsushita Electric Industrial
 of Japan and two electric consumer firms in Hangzhou, Zhejiang
Province, East China, started operations at the Hangzhou Economic
and Technological Development Zone recently.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, which cost an investment of 2.2 billion
Japanese Yen, will produce 1 million electric heaters and gas
cookers a year.
</P>
<P>
Exports up in Zhejiang
</P>
<P>
The export value of farm produce in east China's Zhejiang
Province registered a two-fold increase in the past five years,
reaching 3 billion US dollars by the end of 1995.
</P>
<P>
It has introduced 80 million US dollars to import
agro-technology, and build foreign-funded rural industries.
</P>
<P>
Laver Production
</P>
<P>
Lianyungang, a port city in east China's Jiangsu Province,
exported 28,500 tons of laver which yielded 20 million US
dollars last year, beating all the other provinces in China. Its
products sell well in a dozen of countries and regions including
the United States, Japan and the Republic of Korea. 
</P>
