<DOCNO> XIE19960314.0288 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-14 01:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets Telecommunications Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The country's financial and
trade hub has drawn up a development goal for its
telecommuniations industry for the next five years, with business
expected to be worth 35 billion yuan by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's telecommunications industry aims to have a share of
over 30 percent of the domestic market and export 20 percent of
its products by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The city will focus on developing high-tech products in data
and image transmission, multi-media telecommunications terminals,
telecommunications software, and digital, micro-wave, and mobile
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The sector's output value last year was 12.5 billion yuan, 19
times that of 1990, with 160 million US dollars earned in foreign
currency, and the figure is expected to hit 15 billion yuan this
year.
</P>
<P>
The city has established partnerships with most of the 10
largest telecommunications companies in the world, and signed
agreements on 350 million dollars of foreign investment in its
telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
The city will also take steps to improve local joint ventures,
so as to lower the cost of their products, for a competitive
advantage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
