<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portugal Beats Italy to Qualify for Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Portugal beat Italy 1-0 in the
first leg of a European Under-21 Soccer Championship quarter-final
here on Wednesday, snatching a ticket to the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The winning goal came from striker Hugo Profirio, who took
advantage of a mistake made by Italy's AC Milan star defender
Panucci and headed the ball into the net 18 minutes into the first
half.
</P>
<P>
Panucci chased but failed to control a high ball near the
penalty area, only to see Profirio racing ahead to deliver the
header in the rain.
</P>
<P>
About 30,000 spectators cheered for the home side, which sailed
into the Olympic Games for the second time in 68 years.
</P>
<P>
Portugal qualified last time for the Amsterdam Olympic Games in
1928. 
</P>
</TEXT>
