<HEADLINE> Rural Enterprise Groups to Mushroom in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 14 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has worked out a five-year plan to develop 100 groups of rural
enterprises, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Zhejiang Rural Enterprises Bureau show that
the province has now 880,000 rural enterprises, including over
400 enterprise groups or large companies.
</P>
<P>
Qian Xinhao, director of the bureau, said that the province
will turn some large rural enterprises with good profits into
leading group companies that produce brand-named products.
</P>
<P>
To realize the goals of this plan Zhejiang will invest 25
billion yuan per year.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, some of the province's 400
enterprise groups have become the largest in the country in their
fields. These include the manufacturing of clothing, curtains,
lacquer, and polyester fiber.
</P>
<P>
The largest fodder producer in the province is also a rural
enterprise group, and in the building materials sector half of the
top ten companies are rural enterprise groups. In many other
trades as well, rural enterprise groups are out in front.
</P>
<P>
In 1995 rural enterprises accounted for 75 percent of
Zhejiang's industrial output and 67 percent of provincial
revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
