<HEADLINE> Jalabert Improves Overall Lead in Paris-Nice Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- France's Laurent Jalabert improved
his overall lead by winning his second victory in the fourth stage
of the Paris-Nice cycling race on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Frenchman broke away in the last two kilometers to finish
the 164-kilometer course from Maurs-la-Jolie to Millau in five
hours 16 minutes 08 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Against the strong head winds, Frank Hoj, a 24-year-old Danish
rider, paced for the first 90 kilometers till Levezou where 12
competitors breezed over.
</P>
<P>
Chasing Jalabert in the last dash was American Lance Armstrong
who finished second with 15 seconds behind, and French compatriot
Laurent Brochard ranked third with 22 seconds behind the winner.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Jalabert rode to his first win in stage three, also
beating out Armstrong into second. 
</P>
