<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Defense Minister Leaves for China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav Defense Minister Pavle
Bulatovic left here today for Beijing on a several-day official
visit to China at the invitation of his Chinese counterpart Chi
Haotian.
</P>
<P>
Bulatovic said before his departure that he was certain the
visit would be mutually beneficial and useful.
</P>
<P>
The minister, who is heading a Yugoslav delegation, will
discuss with his host General Chi, who is also Vice-President of
the Central Military Commission of China, the prospects for
strengthening cooperation in military, economic, scientific,
technical, defense and security fields.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav Minister will also visit some Chinese army units,
give a lecture on Yugoslavia's defense system at China's Defense
University, and is expected to be received by top Chinese
officials. 
</P>
