following days of sharp volatility.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 15.17 to 5,568.72.
</P>
<P>
Despite the drop in the Dow, advancers led decliners by 7 to 4,
with 1,536 up, 882 down and 708 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Big Board volume was moderate, standing at 409.47 million
shares.
</P>
<P>
Other market indexes were higher, with the Nasdaq composite
lifted by technology stocks.
</P>
<P>
Transportation stocks were led higher by airline issues.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE's composite index rose 0.47 to 341.86. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500-stock index rose 1.43 638.52.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 14.25 to 1,087.30.
</P>
<P>
At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index rose 1.60
to 560.77.
</P>
<P>
Stocks were helped a little by bonds, where the long bond
yielding was up to 6.67 percent. 
