<HEADLINE> Nigerian Company Assembles Two Cars Of Peugeot 306 A Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Peugeot Automobile Nigeria
(PAN) is producing an average of two cars of its new
model, Peugeot 306, a day, the company's spokesman Alhaji Baba
Yahaya said today in Kaduna, northern Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The company has the capacity to produce 60 cars of the new
model per day, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
On the 306 auto-technology, Alhaji Baba said that Nigerians
were fast acquiring the new technology introduced into Europe in
1993.
</P>
<P>
98 percent of the workforce assembling the car in PAN now are
Nigerians, while the balance are technical advisers.
</P>
<P>
"Already, many Nigerians, comprising staff of our company and
our distributors, have been trained both at home and in Europe on
the 306 technology," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The Peugeot 306 was first launched in December last year by
former Nigerian president Shehu Shagari in Kaduna before it was
introduced into the Lagos and Port Harcourt markets. 
</P>
