<HEADLINE> Hamas Issues Statement Justifying Its Action against Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 13 (Xinhua) -- In its reaction to the
just-concluded "Summit of Peacemakers" in Egypt's Red Sea resort
of Sharm el Sheikh, the Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) today
issued a statement defending its action against Israel.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service
based in east Jerusalem, the statement said, "Hamas is a political
movement against occupation and its actions. It strives to achieve
this through both political and military work."
</P>
<P>
"Hamas Movement believes in political work as well as armed
struggle since each of them has a role in achieving these
rights ... thus it considers the military work of Iz a-Din
Al-Qassam Brigades as defensive measures, except in some
exceptional unintentional cases when it effected civilians, which
contradicts with Hamas' policy," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It continued, "We consider the Israeli presence, in its
various forms, in the West Bank, Jerusalem and Gaza Strip, a
presence of occupation, which U.N. resolutions have continuously
stated and world governments have officially declared since
1967."
</P>
<P>
"U.N. Resolution 242 called on the immediate withdrawal of
Israeli forces from territories it occupied in 1967, but the
Israeli authorities still reject to abide by the text and spirit
of this resolution," it stressed.
</P>
<P>
"The reason for our military apparatus's operations against
Israeli targets is the continued occupation of the Palestinian
territory. This target will spontaneously conclude with the
conclusion of the occupation," it declared.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the Sharm el Sheikh Summit, the Hamas statement
warned: "The international measures supporting the Zionist
position in confronting Hamas will not be the correct approach to
solve the problem, but will be a cause for Israel to continue its
occupation."
</P>
<P>
The statement expressed welcome to any good-will international
mediation, emphasizing, however, that Hamas believes in dialogue
as means for understanding, "but we believe that it is our right
to resist the military occupation and Israeli terror and its
offensive measures against our people." 
</P>
</TEXT>
